3. DOCUMENT STORAGE ğŸ“„
Scenario: Store hotel booking confirmation PDF

Quick Flow:
User uploads PDF â†’ Pinata IPFS â†’ Get CID â†’ Store CID in smart contract
                                        â†“
                              User can download anytime
                              Anyone can verify authenticity
ğŸ’¡ KENAPA PAKAI IPFS?
Without IPFS (All on blockchain):

âŒ Store 1MB image on Ethereum

âŒ Gas cost: ~$50,000+ (insane!)

âŒ Blockchain bloat

âŒ Not scalable
With IPFS:

âœ… Store only 46-byte CID on blockchain

âœ… Gas cost: ~$0.50 (cheap!)

âœ… Actual data on IPFS (pennies)

âœ… Fully decentralized

âœ… Content-addressed (tamper-proof)
ğŸ” SECURITY BENEFITS:
Content Addressing:
CID = Hash of content
If data changes, CID changes
Impossible to tamper without detection
Permanent Storage:
Pinata pins files (won't disappear)
Multiple gateways for redundancy
No single point of failure
Blockchain Verification:
CID stored on-chain = proof of existence
Timestamp = proof of when
Signature = proof of who
